.TH GO 1 "2026-05-06" "Go 1.26.2" "InterGenOS User Manual"
.SH NAME
go \- The Go programming language tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B go
\fIcommand\fR [\fIarguments\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B go
command manages Go source code and runs the Go toolchain.
It provides compilation, testing, dependency management, and
code generation for the Go programming language.
.PP
Common subcommands include:
.TP
.B go build
Compile packages and dependencies.
.TP
.B go run
Compile and run Go programs.
.TP
.B go test
Test packages.
.TP
.B go mod
Module maintenance (add, init, tidy, vendor).
.TP
.B go fmt
Reformat package sources (invokes gofmt).
.TP
.B go vet
Report likely mistakes in packages.
.TP
.B go doc
Show documentation for package or symbol.
.TP
.B go env
Print Go environment information.
.TP
.B go version
Print Go compiler version.
.TP
.B go tool
Run specified Go tool.
.PP
Run
.B go help \fIsubcommand\fP
for detailed usage of a specific subcommand.
Run
.B go
with no arguments for the full command list.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B GOROOT
Root of the Go installation tree (set to
.IR /usr/lib/go ).
.TP
.B GOPATH
Workspace root for Go source code, packages, and binaries.
Defaults to
.IR $HOME/go .
.TP
.B GOBIN
Directory where
.B go install
places compiled binaries.
.TP
.B GOARCH
Target architecture (default
.IR amd64 ).
.TP
.B GOOS
Target operating system (default
.IR linux ).
.TP
.B GOMODCACHE
Directory for downloaded module cache
(Go 1.23+; defaults to
.IR $GOPATH/pkg/mod ).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/lib/go/
Go toolchain installation root.
.TP
.I /usr/bin/go
Symlink to the Go compiler.
.TP
.I $HOME/go/
Default GOPATH workspace directory.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR gofmt (1)
.PP
More documentation at
.UR https://go.dev/doc/
.UE .
.SH BUGS
Report bugs at
.UR https://go.dev/issue/
.UE .
